全栈开发工程师（前端也可以）/Data Engineer（Marketing， BI， big data engineer 三个方向都在招聘），
完全不加班， 福利爆赞，人广附近

【全栈开发工程师（前端也可以）】
Minimum Qualifications
• Bachelor’s degree in computer science/engineering or related major.
• 2+ years of software development experience on web frontend or full stack projects, with a deep understanding of JavaScript, HTML, and CSS.
• Experienced in at least one of the popular modern web frameworks such as ReactJS (preferable), AngularJS, or Vue.js.
• Deep appreciation for design and the overall user experience.
• Enthusiasm about solving business problems with technology and can take ownership of an end-to-end solution.
•Passion for learning new technologies, frameworks, and services.
• Execution mindset and the ability to deliver with cross-functional teams that are globally distributed.
Preferred Qualifications
• Good experience developing in ReactJS and Storybook.
• Experience developing web applications in TypeScript.
• Experience with architecting web applications on modern web stacks.
• Experience with backend service development, with good understanding of large scale distributed systems.
• BA/MS/PhD degree in computer science or a related field preferred.


【Data Engineer （ marketing ）】
（ Marketing，BI，big data engineer 三个方向都在招聘），
Key Responsibilities
• Develop and maintain dashboards with key performance metrics.
• Develop a deep understanding of consumer behaviors and their business implications, convert the insights into products to drive growth.
• Use analytical insights to solve important business problems and formulate robust, actionable recommendations for leadership.
• Utilize excellent communication skills to clearly distill the essence of your technical work to audiences of all levels and across multiple functional areas.
• Contribute to the development of analytical frameworks, tools, and skills.
Qualifications
• Master degree or above in Engineering, Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Finance or related fields.
• 2+ years of work experience involving data analysis, preferably with business analytics / marketing analytics / risk analytics experience
• Strong software programming skills and familiar with at least one programming language. Experience with SQL, Python, and/or modeling skills.
• Passion for finding insights in data and driving change based on those insights.
• Exceptional communication skills; ability to simplify and present complex analytical concepts to senior leadership.
• Fluency in English, both written and oral.
• Work experience with data visualization tools like Tableau, Looker, or Power BI is a plus.
• Knowledge of E-commerce, online payment and mobile a is a strong plus.


【Data Engineer （ BI ）】
What you’ll be doing
Design, development and deliver enterprise analytical data platform, that is able to ingest and transform data at huge scale coming from many different sources, different customers, and in many different varieties
Responsible for analytical datamarts modeling & has knowledge on sourcing data
Develop and maintain dashboards with key performance metrics
Roll out a data governance framework, with a focus on improvement of data quality through standards, governance metrics, processes, related tools and data architecture
Develop collaborative relationships with key business sponsors and IT resources for the efficient resolution of work requests
Contribute to the development of analytical frameworks, tools, and skills
About You
Masters degree or above in Engineering, Computer Science, or related fields
3-5 years of work experience involving data warehouse building, preferably with data modeling and data product experience
Strong software programming skills and familiar with at least one programming language. Experience with SQL, Python
Work experience with data visualization tools like Tableau, Looker, or Power BI is a plus.
Exceptional communication skills; ability to simplify and present complex analytical concepts to audience from multi background
Fluency in English, both written and oral
Knowledge of E-commerce, online payments and mobile a is a strong plus



【Data Engineer （ Big data engineer ）】
Responsibilities
• Design and build self-serving data platform to handle new products and business requirements that securely scale over millions of users and their transactions
• Develop, integrate and optimize end to end data pipeline
• Partner with data scientists, data analysts and domain engineering teams to identify and execute on new opportunities.
Qualifications
• BA/MS/PhD in computer science or a related field
• Experienced in building and maintaining applications that utilize a modern programming language, mainly Java and Python
• Experience with Flink, Kafka, Spark, Cassandra and so on
• Experience with big data cross platform compatible file formats like Apache Avro & Apache Parquet
• Experience with AWS like S3, EMR, Redshift and so on
• Experience on architecturing large scale distributed system
• Enthusiastic about solving business problems with technology and can take ownership of an end-to-end solution
• Passionate about continuously learning new technologies, frameworks, and services
• Possess an execution mindset and the ability to deliver with cross-functional teams that are globally distributed
• Serious about testing and have experience with automated testing frameworks
• Exceptional written and verbal technical communication skills


